      "span_text": "pulsatile nature of crebinostat exposure in the brain may be advantageous for the following reasons: 1) a pulsatile type of exposure may mimic aspects of salient cognitive experiences that occur in short duration yet induce long-lasting memories; 2) pulsatile exposure has been reported to be optimal in inducing neuroprotection [CITATION_1] ; and 3) pulsatile exposure may minimize undesired effects of long-term HDAC inhibition."
